  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>With thunderous simultaneous strikes, you can batter a mighty giant into submission.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Dwarf or gnome; defensive training racial trait; Improved Two-Weapon Fighting and Two-Weapon Fighting, or flurry of blows class feature; Twin Thunders; Twin Thunders Flurry; Weapon Focus with both wielded weapons; base attack bonus +9.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>Whenever you deal an opponent extra damage with the Twin Thunders feat, that opponent is shaken for 1 round. You also force that opponent to succeed at a Fortitude saving throw (DC 10 + half your level + your Str modifier) or become staggered for 1 round. If you use this feat to render staggered an opponent that is already staggered, you daze that opponent instead. In a similar way, you can stun an opponent that is already dazed.<br/><br/><b>Combat Trick</b><br/>When you use the Twin Thunders feat to deal extra damage to an opponent, you can spend 2 stamina points to make that opponent shaken for 1d4 rounds.",
